# Implementation Plan - Balanced Header Distribution

The goal is to redistribute the header information (Company Name, Address, and Contact/Reference details) into a balanced, professional layout that "makes sense" visually. We will move away from the current clumped alignment and implement a horizontally distributed 3-column structure.

## Proposed Changes

### [Component] Header Design (PDF & UI)

#### [MODIFY] [corporatePdf.ts](file:///c:/Apps/Leave%20Tracker/src/lib/corporatePdf.ts)
*   **3-Column Distribution**:
    *   **Left Column**: Logo (anchored at the margin).
    *   **Center Column**: Company name and Address (stacked for clarity).
    *   **Right Column**: Contact details (Tel/Email) and Reference metadata (No/Date) in a compact, right-aligned block.
*   **Vertical Balance**: Adjust the Y-coordinates to ensure all three columns align perfectly at the top and bottom.
*   **Formatting**: Use refined font weights to create a hierarchy (Company Name in bold, others in normal/small).

#### [MODIFY] [Requests.tsx](file:///c:/Apps/Leave%20Tracker/src/pages/Requests.tsx)
*   **Grid Layout**: Use a CSS `grid` or `flexbox` with `justify-content: space-between` to mirror the PDF's 3-column distribution.
*   **Parity**: Ensure font sizes and colors match the PDF exactly for a seamless transition between preview and final document.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> I am proposing a **Horizontal 3-Column Layout** as it is the most standard way to "evenly distribute" this much information without making it look cluttered. 
> 
> **Proposed Structure**:
